        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><b>Broadband - Measuring Availability and Aligning Policies Task Force Act or the Broadband MAPS Act</b></p> <p>This bill requires the Federal Communications Commission (FCC) to establish a task force that oversees implementation and use of broadband availability maps.</p> <p>Specifically, the task force must (1) oversee specified data collection and analysis, including creating and updating broadband availability maps; (2) identify relevant FCC actions and ensure they are informed by the maps; (3) provide cost estimates for maintaining the maps; and (4) provide necessary recommendations to ensure the FCC can produce sufficiently granular and accurate maps to determine areas that lack broadband internet access service.</p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
